<LEADPARA>  QUESTION: Can you please tell me if ALF of the series of the same name is a
real small person, a robot or an animated puppet?;    ANSWER: "ALF" is a
combination of special effects and mechanical wizardry that involves many
people. To this day, the producers refuse to divulge the secrets of his
operation. In fact, they still insist that their publicists say that ALF
really is an alien when asked this question.  </LEADPARA>
<SECTION>  TV Magazine  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  MYSTERY OF ALF REMAINS INTACT  </HEADLINE>
<MEMO>  Celebrity Questions  </MEMO>
<TEXT>     Q: Are there any plans to make a sequel to "The Sound of Music"?;    A:
There have been lots of plans (including a von Trapp family movie by producer
Michael Viner) but nothing is close to being executed. This is at least in
part because of legal complications with rights owned by the estate of Oscar
Hammerstein (who with Richard Rodgers composed the musical). The remaining
real-life von Trapps own and operate a family lodge in Stowe, Vt. There Maria,
wearing her familiar Swiss costume, gladly signed autographs until her death
in 1987 at the age of 82.;    Q: I am a big fan of Alyssa Milano (Samantha) of
the sitcom "Who's the Boss?" Can you tell me if she has played in any movies?;
   A: The 18-year-old actress's first feature film was "Old Enough," which won
awards at the 1984 Cannes Film Festival, after which she co-starred with
Arnold Schwarzenegger in "Commando" and with Sir John Gielgud in "The
Canterville Ghost." Right now she is in production on a comedy tentatively
titled "Coed" with Jonathan Silverman and plans to begin work in February on a
Spanish movie titled "Of Love and Shadows." Making "Coed" means juggling time:
"Boss" by day, "Coed" nights and weekends, with her senior year of high school
sandwiched in-between.;    Q: I loved Sage Stallone in "Rocky V." Could you
please tell me more about him?;    A: The older of Sylvester and ex-wife Sasha
Stallone's two sons, 14-year-old Sage is a film fan who takes and edits his
own home movies. He's an exercise enthusiast and also enjoys skiing, music,
reading, travel and cars. Younger brother Seargeoh, 11, is autistic, which has
led the rest of the Stallone family to involvement in fund-raising activities
on behalf of autism research.  </TEXT>
